From cou.: 7 For the instrument used in this study and possibly in other systems, an applied power of 1.2 kW without a water load causes a secondary discharge to form beyond the sampling cone, i.e., in the last skimmer region of the ion optics for this particular system. While the exact nature of the discharge is still not understood,7–9 a substantial current flows from the skimmer cone to ground (0.1–0.5 mA). The discharge also causes a marked decrease in the signal intensity and can lead to erosion of the second skimmer cone.10 It was found that a reduction of the applied power from 1.2 kW to 0.7 kW minimizes or eliminates the discharge while maximizing the sensitivity for dry plasma conditions.9,10 In brief, this need for reduced power operation with dry sample introduction further supports the requirement for optimization in the absence of solvent.
From Soup: 7 For the instrument used in this study and possibly in other systems, an applied power of 1.2 kW without a water load causes a secondary discharge to form beyond the sampling cone, i.e. , in the last skimmer region of the ion optics for this particular system. While the exact nature of the discharge is still not understood, 7–9 a substantial current flows from the skimmer cone to ground (0.1–0.5 mA). The discharge also causes a marked decrease in the signal intensity and can lead to erosion of the second skimmer cone. 10 It was found that a reduction of the applied power from 1.2 kW to 0.7 kW minimizes or eliminates the discharge while maximizing the sensitivity for dry plasma conditions. 9,10 In brief, this need for reduced power operation with dry sample introduction further supports the requirement for optimization in the absence of solvent .
