From Soup: 31 It should be stressed that the response algorithm used for optimization can be structured to reflect the analyst’s tuning objectives. For example, if one wished to optimize the sensitivity of the heavy elements, all masses could be used but W m / z for heavier masses could be made disproportionately large. Thus, small changes in the intensity of the larger m / z calibrants would show a favorable change in R even when accompanied by an intensity loss for the low mass ions.
