From cou.: 40 ε
From Soup: 40 A schematic of the dry calibrator is illustrated in Fig. 1 . The halide salts were loaded into separate columns, and gas flow through each column were controlled via needle valves. The Pb signal required a balance between flow rates and filament current to achieve the desired signal. A metered bypass line (second line from the bottom in Fig. 1 ) permitted adjustment of the total central channel flow to a predetermined value once the flows for the individual elements were adjusted.
